WEBVTT

00:08.641 --> 00:10.944
[electronic dance music playing]

00:14.814 --> 00:18.351
[people chattering]

00:26.326 --> 00:28.695
[music continues]

00:35.168 --> 00:37.504
[chatter continues]

00:40.306 --> 00:42.242
You're gonna save me one, right?

00:42.308 --> 00:46.046
- All right! Later!
- Follow me! Whoo!

00:46.112 --> 00:47.680
Go, go, go!
We've got this, guys.

00:47.747 --> 00:49.382
- Let's go.
- We can do it, come on.

00:49.482 --> 00:51.084
I'm right behind you.

00:52.285 --> 00:55.088
Avoid any eye contact.

00:55.155 --> 00:58.191
Uh, where are you going?
How old are you?

00:58.291 --> 00:59.826
Sixteen.

00:59.926 --> 01:01.428
Yeah, right.
You're all 16.

01:01.528 --> 01:03.596
Beat it, kids.
Don't stand in the way.

01:04.464 --> 01:07.467
QUINO: Man.

01:07.567 --> 01:11.871
Mr. Bouncer, could we speak
for a moment in private?

01:11.971 --> 01:13.406
Stay right there.

01:14.474 --> 01:15.875
What do you want?

01:15.942 --> 01:20.713
Well, we may not be 16,
but just look at me.

01:20.814 --> 01:23.917
I'll never compete in a marathon
or play football with my son.

01:23.983 --> 01:27.454
But you know
what I'm able to do?

01:27.520 --> 01:28.555
Party like an animal
with my friends

01:28.655 --> 01:29.989
at the greatest damn party
of the year.

01:30.090 --> 01:33.326
What do you say, man?
Just let us in?

01:33.393 --> 01:36.362
[music continues]

01:36.429 --> 01:37.797
Hey!

01:42.268 --> 01:46.106
I told him we'll pass.
It's very noisy inside.

01:46.206 --> 01:48.842
Of course it's very noisy.
That's what clubs are like.

01:48.908 --> 01:50.610
A match at the arcade
sounds phat.

01:50.677 --> 01:52.245
- Let's do that.
- How much cash did you bring?

01:52.312 --> 01:53.847
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

01:53.913 --> 01:55.215
- So, we're broke?
- There's money at your house.

01:55.281 --> 01:56.883
We could, but yours is closer.

01:56.950 --> 01:58.251
And nobody's there.

01:58.318 --> 01:59.786
Hey! Sandra!

02:01.988 --> 02:05.758
- Why are you here? Huh, kiddo?
- Get us in.

02:05.825 --> 02:08.294
Do you think I just have
a spare ticket for no reason?

02:11.965 --> 02:13.433
Whoa!

02:20.006 --> 02:21.374
It's perfect.

02:22.575 --> 02:23.843
Let's go party.
Come on.

02:23.910 --> 02:25.111
[horn honking]

02:25.211 --> 02:25.912
Later!

02:26.012 --> 02:29.082
Hey, do you only have one?

02:29.149 --> 02:30.683
Tough decision, kiddo.

02:32.252 --> 02:35.588
Psst, psst.
Don't even think about it.

02:35.688 --> 02:37.490
You've gotta get in.

02:37.557 --> 02:39.826
Yeah, and then you can tell
if it's the bomb, dude,

02:39.926 --> 02:41.694
as everyone says.

02:41.761 --> 02:43.930
So you can beat our "Street
Fighter" record without me?

02:43.997 --> 02:47.534
There's no way.
Let's bounce.

02:59.679 --> 03:02.015
Sandra! Sandra!

03:02.081 --> 03:04.284
[overlapping chatter]

03:07.921 --> 03:11.491
[singing in Spanish]

04:23.997 --> 04:26.165
Geez. You have to let me know
where you're going, Bea.

04:26.232 --> 04:28.735
- Sorry, it was...
- Do you feel okay?

04:28.801 --> 04:30.470
Come on.

05:01.601 --> 05:05.705
♪♪♪

05:35.335 --> 05:37.670
[monitor beeping]

05:46.112 --> 05:47.714
What's that tube for?

05:49.148 --> 05:51.451
To help him breathe, I guess.

05:57.023 --> 05:59.125
Do you remember
when he had pneumonia,

05:59.192 --> 06:01.327
and spent Christmas
in this hospital?

06:04.464 --> 06:06.632
And then the experiment
at the science lab.

06:06.733 --> 06:10.036
[chuckles]
He got burned all over his arm.

06:10.136 --> 06:13.206
And that time with the vault
at the P.E. class.

06:13.272 --> 06:15.041
- He even lost a tooth.
- Two teeth.

06:15.108 --> 06:16.676
Yeah, you're right.

06:29.422 --> 06:31.991
How is he?

06:32.091 --> 06:33.426
We've been here all day,
and no one's told us anything.

06:33.526 --> 06:37.764
We've been running some tests,
and I won't lie to you.

06:37.830 --> 06:40.633
His condition is serious.
He inhaled too much smoke

06:40.733 --> 06:42.869
and he's breathing
with difficulty.

06:42.969 --> 06:46.272
The next three to four hours
are critical to his condition.

06:46.372 --> 06:48.107
We need to keep our hopes up.

06:58.351 --> 07:00.720
[monitor beeping]

07:11.330 --> 07:13.399
Come on, Alvaro.
Wake up.

07:17.837 --> 07:19.472
You have to wake up.

07:24.911 --> 07:27.713
Javi, do you think
he'll pull through?

07:27.814 --> 07:31.250
I don't know, Quino.
I don't know.

07:31.317 --> 07:32.585
Get over here,
you motherfucker!

07:32.685 --> 07:33.886
- Stop! Stop!
QUINO: Hey, hey, hey!

07:33.953 --> 07:35.655
Why the hell did you have to go
in there, huh?

07:35.721 --> 07:36.956
- Stop it, moron!
- Stay out of it,

07:37.056 --> 07:38.591
- you little maggot!
- Don't touch him, dipshit!

07:38.691 --> 07:40.193
What?!
My mom's feeling miserable.

07:40.293 --> 07:41.994
And if that asshole, Morte,
hurts her,

07:42.094 --> 07:43.329
- it'll be your fault, moron.
- Let him go!

07:43.396 --> 07:45.164
Is that clear?
[both scream]

07:45.231 --> 07:46.933
[electrical zapping]

07:46.999 --> 07:49.135
[siren wailing]

07:49.202 --> 07:51.671
That was blood-curdling as hell.
I almost shit my pants.

07:51.771 --> 07:52.672
ZETA: Damn it.

07:52.772 --> 07:54.807
You miserable rats
screwed my life.

07:54.874 --> 07:56.175
JAVI: No, we didn't.

07:56.242 --> 07:59.078
No one made you
follow us to Paraiso.

07:59.145 --> 08:01.214
You died with the classroom
nerds, deal with it.

08:05.384 --> 08:06.719
Where are you going?

08:06.786 --> 08:07.753
To search every basement
in this town.

08:07.854 --> 08:10.556
My sister has to be somewhere.

08:10.623 --> 08:11.591
QUINO: Wait for me, Javi.

08:11.691 --> 08:14.026
Don't leave me alone
with this guy.

08:14.126 --> 08:15.127
ZETA: Fucking great.

08:26.672 --> 08:27.673
ROCA: You don't have
to tell them anything!

08:27.773 --> 08:29.442
BEA: But I do, I have to.
Please, Dad!

08:29.509 --> 08:30.910
- No. I said no.
- Come on, it'll just take

08:31.010 --> 08:31.944
- 10 minutes.
- And I won't say it again!

08:32.044 --> 08:33.279
It'll just take 10 damn minutes.

08:33.346 --> 08:34.480
- Go to your room now.
- Let me go.

08:34.547 --> 08:36.616
- Just let me--
- [grunts]

08:36.682 --> 08:37.650
You're not going anywhere,

08:37.717 --> 08:39.385
and you're not speaking
to anyone.

08:39.485 --> 08:41.053
You can't stop me.
You're not my owner.

08:41.120 --> 08:43.155
I'm your father. If I hadn't
stopped you yesterday,

08:43.256 --> 08:44.824
you'd be dead right now!

08:44.924 --> 08:47.126
It might not be such a bad thing
now that you mention it.

08:47.193 --> 08:49.629
Listen, Bea.
[sighs]

08:51.864 --> 08:53.533
[scoffs]

08:53.599 --> 08:55.368
- [door slams]
- [sighs]

08:58.204 --> 09:00.172
[exhales]

09:08.047 --> 09:10.850
[electrical zapping]

09:10.917 --> 09:13.286
[TV playing faintly]

09:17.089 --> 09:19.025
REPORTER:<i> Yesterday,</i>
<i>almost 2,000 villagers</i>

09:19.125 --> 09:22.094
<i>attended the funeral
of the young victim,</i>

09:22.161 --> 09:23.796
<i>who was allegedly murdered
by one of her classmates</i>

09:23.863 --> 09:27.733
<i>between 2:00 and 4:00 p.m.</i>

09:27.800 --> 09:29.969
<i>The village ceased
every single activity</i>

09:30.036 --> 09:33.072
<i>as a sign of protest
for the minor's death.</i>

09:33.172 --> 09:36.475
<i>A plague of African moths
has invaded the region.</i>

09:36.542 --> 09:37.643
<i>The environment ministry
has set out</i>

09:37.710 --> 09:40.212
<i>a moth eradication plan,
as the plague</i>

09:40.279 --> 09:42.281
<i>could affect
the region's crops.</i>

09:42.348 --> 09:44.784
<i>Neighbors have found
hundreds of them in their homes</i>

09:44.884 --> 09:45.885
<i>as they're attracted
to their lights.</i>

09:45.952 --> 09:48.921
<i>They are called
silver gamma.</i>

09:48.988 --> 09:50.790
<i>These 1.5-inch-long moths</i>

09:50.890 --> 09:52.491
<i>are brown colored
with a white pattern</i>

09:52.558 --> 09:53.793
<i>over the wings
that resembles the form</i>

09:53.893 --> 09:56.963
<i>of the Greek letter Gamma,
hence their name.</i>

09:57.029 --> 09:58.731
<i>Despite their peculiar
appearance,</i>

09:58.798 --> 10:00.032
<i>they are not dangerous,
but are considered annoying</i>

10:00.132 --> 10:02.268
<i>by the residents
of the affected areas.</i>

10:02.368 --> 10:05.571
<i>Experts recommend keeping
doors and windows</i>

10:05.638 --> 10:08.374
<i>shut during the night
until the plague subsides,</i>

10:08.441 --> 10:09.742
<i>which is likely to persist</i>

10:09.842 --> 10:11.611
<i>for another few days
in our country.</i>

10:11.677 --> 10:13.713
<i>Thirty-three people
have been injured</i>

10:13.813 --> 10:15.314
<i>in an accident on the so-called
Highway of Death.</i>

10:15.414 --> 10:18.884
<i>Six victims have been taken
to the local hospital</i>

10:18.951 --> 10:20.152
<i>in critical condition.</i>

10:20.252 --> 10:23.089
<i>In other news,
experts investigate...</i>

10:23.155 --> 10:25.825
How about the one you bought
him for Manu's wedding?

10:25.925 --> 10:29.562
<i>...which was discovered
in a valley in Southern France.</i>

10:29.629 --> 10:31.364
<i>The rock formation
was discovered</i>

10:31.430 --> 10:33.399
<i>by three cave explorers</i>

10:33.466 --> 10:35.568
<i>after removing the rubble
of stones</i>

10:35.635 --> 10:37.069
<i>that blocked a passage.</i>

10:39.972 --> 10:41.574
<i>The cave is extensive,</i>

10:41.641 --> 10:44.410
<i>about 400 yards long
with vast chambers.</i>

10:44.477 --> 10:46.445
<i>The floor of the cave
is littered with...</i>

10:46.512 --> 10:48.481
Do you want something to eat?

10:48.547 --> 10:51.050
A coffee or a tea?
Whatever you want.

10:53.953 --> 10:55.955
But you have to eat, Mario.

10:57.390 --> 10:59.759
[phone ringing]

11:10.236 --> 11:12.104
Hello?

11:12.204 --> 11:13.606
Hi, Dad.

11:13.673 --> 11:16.275
No, I can't right now.
What is it?

11:16.375 --> 11:17.543
Samuel?

11:19.045 --> 11:21.313
- Tell him I'll call back later.
- I told him to get help.

11:44.603 --> 11:47.606
"Get out of my sight."
That's what I said.

11:50.142 --> 11:53.646
All for that motorbike
which is still here.

11:57.983 --> 11:59.585
But he's not.

12:01.954 --> 12:03.856
Dad, I haven't left.

12:07.960 --> 12:10.563
None of that really matters.

12:10.629 --> 12:12.765
He knew you loved him.

12:14.366 --> 12:15.768
Undeniably.

12:37.790 --> 12:39.792
<i>Three young boys
have passed away,</i>

12:39.892 --> 12:41.127
<i>and the condition of another
is profoundly severe</i>

12:41.193 --> 12:43.796
<i>after a fire accident
in a nightclub</i>

12:43.863 --> 12:45.798
<i>on the outskirts
of their hometown.</i>

12:45.865 --> 12:48.834
<i>All between 13 and 15 years old.</i>

12:48.934 --> 12:50.636
Don't even say it
or I'll smack you.

12:50.736 --> 12:51.971
<i>The property belongs
to a foreign firm</i>

12:52.037 --> 12:54.807
<i>that has been unwilling
to comment on the causes</i>

12:54.874 --> 12:57.643
<i>of this tragedy, but everything
points at it being</i>

12:57.710 --> 13:00.613
<i>a very unfortunate accident.</i>

13:00.679 --> 13:04.116
<i>This club remains closed
during the entire winter season,</i>

13:04.183 --> 13:06.719
<i>and it is known for being a
popular nighttime drinking spot</i>

13:06.786 --> 13:08.721
<i>amongst local teenagers.</i>

13:08.788 --> 13:10.723
<i>It is believed
that it might be the reason</i>

13:10.790 --> 13:12.925
<i>why these young boys were there.</i>

13:12.992 --> 13:15.361
But-- but what kind
of bullshit is that?

13:15.427 --> 13:17.129
What about the tunnel that we--

13:17.196 --> 13:19.665
<i>Today, Almanzora's community
mourns their young.</i>

13:19.765 --> 13:21.033
<i>The authorities
have joined citizens...</i>

13:21.133 --> 13:21.967
- Zeta?
<i>- ...as flags are flying</i>

13:22.034 --> 13:24.870
<i>at half-mast at the town hall.</i>

13:24.970 --> 13:27.106
<i>A huge number
of friends and relatives</i>

13:27.206 --> 13:29.909
<i>decided to honor the kids
by leaving tokens of support</i>

13:30.009 --> 13:31.644
<i>and their condolences.</i>

13:39.585 --> 13:40.786
Javi?

13:51.997 --> 13:55.534
Javi, you've seen the news,
right?

13:57.903 --> 13:59.772
But how did it close?

13:59.839 --> 14:01.307
[electrical zapping]

14:01.407 --> 14:03.075
The lid won't move
unless you press that,

14:03.175 --> 14:05.110
and none of us did.

14:05.211 --> 14:06.812
[zapping]

14:06.879 --> 14:08.047
[sighs]

14:12.051 --> 14:14.453
I think someone else
was here at the club with us

14:14.520 --> 14:16.889
and came in here
and closed the chest.

14:16.956 --> 14:19.191
My sister was taken
by the same man.

14:21.694 --> 14:23.495
I think it's fucked up
that he could've saved us all...

14:25.598 --> 14:27.199
but he would rather
have us burned alive

14:27.266 --> 14:28.601
than getting caught.

14:30.135 --> 14:31.670
That piece of shit.

14:32.905 --> 14:34.573
A big and fat shit.

14:34.640 --> 14:36.976
[motorbike engine revving]

14:48.988 --> 14:51.757
- How did you do that?
- I got on it and "poof!"

14:51.824 --> 14:53.826
But that's impossible.
The rules don't work like that.

14:53.926 --> 14:56.028
I don't give a fuck
about the rules.

14:56.128 --> 14:57.730
I'm out of here, lame-os.

15:08.407 --> 15:10.242
Shadowfax.

15:10.309 --> 15:12.711
- What?
- When Gandalf the Great dies,

15:12.811 --> 15:15.214
he comes back as Gandalf
the freaking White, right?

15:15.281 --> 15:17.516
- Do you remember that?
- No.

15:17.583 --> 15:20.519
Unexpectedly,
Shadowfax comes to the rescue.

15:20.586 --> 15:23.489
King of horses, bred and adored
by the kings of Rohan.

15:23.555 --> 15:25.824
His old horse friend,
but white and unpolluted, dude.

15:25.925 --> 15:28.127
The best version of it.
[chuckles]

15:28.193 --> 15:30.129
Dude, they've got it
figured out.

15:33.966 --> 15:35.534
Hey.

15:39.405 --> 15:41.774
♪♪♪

16:22.681 --> 16:23.782
Yeah! [laughs]

16:23.882 --> 16:27.753
- [both laughing]
- Yeah!

16:27.853 --> 16:29.488
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

16:29.555 --> 16:31.390
Oh, crap.

16:31.490 --> 16:35.094
[bells tolling]

16:55.514 --> 16:56.482
[sniffling]

17:08.093 --> 17:09.828
[laughing]

17:15.934 --> 17:18.103
[doorbell rings]

17:25.411 --> 17:26.412
Hello.
I need to speak to Mario.

17:26.478 --> 17:28.814
Both of you.

17:28.881 --> 17:30.282
Sure, come in.

17:32.751 --> 17:35.788
- Javi found something.
- What happened?

17:35.888 --> 17:38.390
We found a badge in the side
of the cliff near Paraiso.

17:38.490 --> 17:41.326
- But no one can go down there.
- Go on.

17:41.393 --> 17:43.595
We gave it to your father,
but he dismissed it,

17:43.695 --> 17:46.331
and Javi was sure
it was Sandra's.

17:46.398 --> 17:48.133
And that the Ireland story
is alive

17:48.200 --> 17:49.735
because the girls
didn't run away.

17:51.170 --> 17:53.672
And then Javi found a ticket
that belonged to Sandra.

17:55.407 --> 17:56.742
What ticket?

17:56.842 --> 17:59.311
They all were planning
to see Mecano.

17:59.411 --> 18:01.713
Who runs away
before a concert so important?

18:02.815 --> 18:04.249
I just don't know.

18:04.316 --> 18:06.585
But what if Javi's theories
are right?

18:07.853 --> 18:09.988
I think they found something
at the club that night.

18:10.089 --> 18:12.524
I mean, that fire.

18:12.591 --> 18:14.593
Isn't it too much
of a coincidence?

19:17.122 --> 19:19.491
♪♪♪

19:26.465 --> 19:28.834
[clock chiming]

19:34.473 --> 19:36.808
[sighs]

19:40.679 --> 19:42.814
[exhales sharply]

19:55.360 --> 19:57.763
Nana.

20:00.465 --> 20:02.000
Friends of yours?

20:03.669 --> 20:05.571
Same school.

20:05.637 --> 20:07.005
[sighs]

20:07.072 --> 20:10.676
This job has always been
a ballbuster.

20:12.010 --> 20:14.313
Especially with children.

20:14.413 --> 20:17.482
It's a bitch,
a fucking sad bitch.

20:19.885 --> 20:21.520
Have I ever told you
that my brother

20:21.587 --> 20:23.722
was also around that age
when he passed away?

20:23.789 --> 20:25.524
A million times, Nana.

20:25.591 --> 20:28.360
And before you get going again,
I'm off.

20:28.427 --> 20:30.562
Are you going to the funeral?

20:30.629 --> 20:31.763
Mm-hmm.

20:31.830 --> 20:33.432
- Shall I pick you up?
- Mm-hmm.

20:33.532 --> 20:34.833
Okay.

20:35.968 --> 20:37.436
Wait a minute. Hey.

20:37.502 --> 20:39.304
[scoffs]
What?

20:39.404 --> 20:41.240
Has your Aunt Flo
visited you, my dear?

20:41.306 --> 20:43.508
Who?

20:43.609 --> 20:45.344
Well, Bloody Mary
or lady business.

20:45.444 --> 20:47.446
- That time of the month.
- Why did I ever ask?

20:47.512 --> 20:49.681
No, Nana.
Thanks for reminding me

20:49.748 --> 20:51.283
that I'm behind the schedule.

20:51.350 --> 20:53.518
[scoffs]
Any more questions,

20:53.585 --> 20:56.288
or should we discuss
my vaginal discharge?

20:57.389 --> 20:58.924
[chuckles lightly]

21:00.626 --> 21:02.094
[gum pops]

21:13.272 --> 21:15.641
♪♪♪

21:24.483 --> 21:26.852
[monitor beeping]

21:40.565 --> 21:43.201
What I wouldn't give
for a Pink Panther Bar now.

21:43.268 --> 21:45.904
Or a Bollycao.
[sighs]

21:46.004 --> 21:47.773
With delicious chocolate
pouring from it.

21:49.007 --> 21:51.543
Damn it.
[sighs]

21:54.846 --> 21:56.915
How's he doing?

21:57.015 --> 21:58.750
Hasn't changed.

22:08.727 --> 22:09.828
No way.

22:09.928 --> 22:12.331
That's my friend Pep's
super-hot neighbor.

22:21.506 --> 22:23.575
He's pulled his pud
so hard for her.

22:23.642 --> 22:25.610
He doesn't get tired
of looking at that babe.

22:27.512 --> 22:29.014
Damn.

22:29.081 --> 22:30.849
JAVI: I'm not surprised.

22:35.654 --> 22:38.523
Hey, guys, guys.
What's your favorite poison?

22:38.590 --> 22:41.360
A Pink Panther
or a Bollycao?

22:45.430 --> 22:47.366
[sighs]

22:47.432 --> 22:49.801
[monitor beeping]

22:56.274 --> 22:59.678
- [monitor beeping rapidly]
- What is that?

23:01.012 --> 23:02.681
Bitch, what'd you do?

23:02.748 --> 23:04.249
- What happened?
- I don't know.

23:04.316 --> 23:06.284
I was checking his temperature
when the convulsions started.

23:06.351 --> 23:07.919
You fucking liar.

23:10.689 --> 23:12.224
- [long, steady beep]
- His heart is failing.

23:12.324 --> 23:14.226
One milligram
of epinephrine quickly.

23:14.326 --> 23:16.094
Get the charge ready.

23:16.161 --> 23:18.730
We're losing him!

23:18.797 --> 23:20.465
Come on, quickly!

23:22.868 --> 23:23.935
And clear!

24:35.774 --> 24:37.676
[Javi grunting]

24:40.879 --> 24:43.248
[yelling]

25:01.833 --> 25:05.070
[screaming]

25:19.284 --> 25:20.552
[coughing]

25:20.652 --> 25:22.921
ZETA: Javi!

25:22.988 --> 25:23.388
Zeta!

25:23.488 --> 25:26.758
[coughing]

25:33.064 --> 25:34.833
ZETA: What the hell happened?

25:45.076 --> 25:47.712
Hey, take a chill pill.
He's okay, all good.

25:47.812 --> 25:49.447
They helped him,
he's stabilizing.

25:49.514 --> 25:52.751
- Where were you two?
- The basement.

25:52.851 --> 25:54.486
That woman tried
to kill me, Quino.

25:54.553 --> 25:55.987
Kill you?
What do you mean?

25:56.087 --> 25:58.890
Well, she grabbed me by the neck
with one hand.

25:58.957 --> 26:02.761
And with the other, I think
she tried to rip my heart out.

26:02.827 --> 26:04.429
Like in "Indiana Jones"?

26:04.529 --> 26:07.532
Yeah.
And then she turned old.

26:07.599 --> 26:10.435
Like those videos where
an apple rots in fast motion.

26:10.535 --> 26:12.370
And how did she do it?
Was she a ghost as well?

26:12.437 --> 26:14.639
No, because everyone saw her.
But you're dead.

26:14.706 --> 26:16.274
- Why would she try and--
- I don't know, Quino.

26:16.374 --> 26:17.909
I just don't know.

26:18.009 --> 26:20.645
I don't know how
or why, okay?

26:20.712 --> 26:22.447
But that's exactly
what happened.

26:24.282 --> 26:25.850
She tried to kill me.

26:25.917 --> 26:28.453
And you know what?
She almost did.

26:39.030 --> 26:41.199
What the hell's going on?

26:41.266 --> 26:44.369
You know, the problem is not
that we're fucking clueless.

26:44.436 --> 26:47.172
The problem is
we have no one to ask.

26:47.238 --> 26:48.873
You're right.

26:48.974 --> 26:51.509
Where are the other ghosts
hiding?

26:51.610 --> 26:55.146
- What other ghosts, Quino?
- The ones in the movies.

26:55.246 --> 26:56.748
A guide, at least.

26:56.848 --> 26:58.316
The typical ghost
that shows up

26:58.383 --> 27:00.318
and explains stuff
like a tour guide.

27:00.385 --> 27:03.888
Like, uh, like... like that guy
at the subway in "Ghost."

27:09.227 --> 27:11.129
What?

27:11.196 --> 27:12.163
Follow me.

27:12.230 --> 27:15.000
- Where are you going?
- Let's go!

27:15.066 --> 27:16.601
Wait, Javi.
Damnit!

27:16.668 --> 27:18.103
What are you trying to say?
Watch your tone with me.

27:18.203 --> 27:19.471
You're just wasting
fucking time!

27:19.571 --> 27:20.805
What do you want me to do
in this case?

27:20.872 --> 27:21.873
You have to consider
our son, Dora.

27:21.973 --> 27:23.174
What's that supposed to mean?

27:23.241 --> 27:25.143
This is not my fault.

27:36.688 --> 27:38.890
[line ringing]

27:38.957 --> 27:40.225
Oh!

27:49.000 --> 27:50.468
Samuel?

27:50.568 --> 27:53.438
Hi. This is Paula.
Paula Costa.

27:53.505 --> 27:56.274
I'm calling because I know
I said that I would,

27:56.374 --> 28:00.278
but I won't be able to accept
the job you offered me.

28:00.345 --> 28:03.515
I know.
I know, and I apologize, but...

28:04.849 --> 28:08.853
Um, well, something's come up
and, no, I won't make it.

28:08.920 --> 28:10.655
Not for now, I'm afraid.

28:12.490 --> 28:14.559
Thank you again.

28:14.626 --> 28:15.794
Wait.
Samuel, I'm curious.

28:15.894 --> 28:18.830
Did someone mention
an epidemic at the coast?

28:20.865 --> 28:23.334
Does a toxic spill
ring any bells?

28:23.401 --> 28:24.469
Hmm. I see.

28:24.569 --> 28:27.305
Thanks anyway.

28:27.405 --> 28:29.874
I appreciate it, Samuel.
Bye.

28:52.130 --> 28:53.598
[scoffs]

28:54.733 --> 28:56.601
RAMON:<i> Charlie, do you copy?</i>

28:58.970 --> 29:00.472
<i>Honey, are you there?</i>

29:00.572 --> 29:01.806
[sighs]

29:03.408 --> 29:05.043
I copy.
What's up?

29:05.110 --> 29:08.246
<i>Alvaro's woken up,
and he's asking for you.</i>

29:09.647 --> 29:11.249
Of course.
I'm on my way.

29:17.355 --> 29:19.724
[wings fluttering]

29:50.188 --> 29:51.556
[electrical zapping]

30:16.681 --> 30:18.750
MARIA: I miss him so much.
[sobs]

30:18.850 --> 30:20.518
Quino?

30:20.585 --> 30:23.321
[sobbing continues]

30:23.388 --> 30:26.991
I waited for him all night.
[sobbing]

30:49.214 --> 30:51.549
[soft chattering]

32:39.390 --> 32:41.559
I felt a very strong pain.

32:41.626 --> 32:43.328
After or before the nausea?

33:14.158 --> 33:16.094
What the hell happened?

33:16.160 --> 33:17.962
I'm sorry, I don't know.

33:18.029 --> 33:20.531
He had woken up,
but not for long.

33:21.599 --> 33:24.135
He had another crisis,
and this time he--

33:24.202 --> 33:25.636
he didn't make it.

33:25.703 --> 33:28.072
[Dora sobbing]

33:56.968 --> 33:58.436
Crappy funeral.

33:58.503 --> 34:00.872
I'm off to the next life
with a Bible and a rosary.

34:00.972 --> 34:01.506
Our classmates
would kick the crap out of me

34:01.606 --> 34:04.308
if they saw this.

34:04.409 --> 34:06.477
[phone ringing]

34:06.544 --> 34:08.079
In the graveyard
we found nothing,

34:08.146 --> 34:09.480
nor here apparently.

34:10.615 --> 34:12.383
Any idea
where we can go looking?

34:15.119 --> 34:17.054
Yes. Quiñones Funeral Home.

34:19.390 --> 34:21.826
Sure. Bring him over.

34:21.926 --> 34:24.529
I'll get him ready so that he
can be buried with his friends.

34:29.600 --> 34:32.904
What happened now?

34:33.004 --> 34:35.840
He didn't pull through.
It couldn't be clearer.

34:40.478 --> 34:42.847
[choir singing]

35:03.367 --> 35:05.703
[singing continues]

35:24.789 --> 35:27.992
[sobbing]

35:58.356 --> 36:01.092
- [horn beeping]
- Shit.

36:08.566 --> 36:11.202
[horn beeps]

36:14.772 --> 36:17.408
JAVI:<i> Please, Dad, come on.</i>

36:17.475 --> 36:19.043
<i>I wanna sit in the front.</i>

36:19.110 --> 36:21.045
MARIO:<i> [scoffs]</i>
<i>What's the matter now, Javi?</i>

36:21.112 --> 36:22.480
It's my turn to go up front.

36:22.547 --> 36:24.348
She snuck in
when I went for my hat.

36:24.448 --> 36:26.250
You snooze, you lose,
little brother.

36:26.317 --> 36:27.885
What?
Do you see?

36:27.952 --> 36:29.387
She's crossing the line, Dad.
Tell me what to do.

36:29.487 --> 36:30.521
That's right, Sandra,
don't tease your brother.

36:30.588 --> 36:32.323
Move your feet, lose your seat?

36:32.390 --> 36:33.925
No, you know what you are.
You're a bully and you're ugly.

36:33.991 --> 36:35.560
No, seriously, tell her.
Let me go in the front seat.

36:35.626 --> 36:37.328
- You two work it out, okay?
- You can sit here later.

36:37.395 --> 36:38.963
- No, it's my turn. No. Now.
- No. No.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.932
But, Dad, come on. Help me.

36:40.998 --> 36:43.267
No, seriously,
Sandra, that's not fair.

36:43.367 --> 36:46.571
- Later.
- No. Dad!

36:48.806 --> 36:50.041
Go forward.

36:58.583 --> 37:02.987
♪♪♪

37:14.865 --> 37:18.436
[choir singing]

37:33.751 --> 37:35.686
This is absolutely pointless.

38:23.234 --> 38:25.903
[sobbing]

38:33.344 --> 38:34.912
Where's your dad?

38:37.815 --> 38:39.550
And I haven't seen Costa.

39:02.773 --> 39:05.376
- [knocking]
MARIO: Perez!

39:05.443 --> 39:07.078
[door opens]

39:09.480 --> 39:12.016
Gil Perez?

39:47.084 --> 39:49.687
[clanking]

40:50.080 --> 40:52.450
[sobbing]

40:56.053 --> 40:59.089
[sobbing continues]

41:55.613 --> 41:59.083
And the breaking point--
the missing rat.

42:25.543 --> 42:27.611
Anyone would say
you're not glad to see me, huh?

42:27.678 --> 42:29.146
Stool pigeon.

43:22.199 --> 43:25.769
[sobbing]

44:13.050 --> 44:14.985
♪♪♪

44:15.085 --> 44:17.054
QUINO: I can walk!

44:20.424 --> 44:23.027
Yeah!
I can jump!

44:23.127 --> 44:24.028
Up! Up!
Woohoo!

44:24.128 --> 44:27.431
Look! Javi, Javi!
Who's the king?

44:27.531 --> 44:29.633
I am, sir!
Everybody down!

44:29.733 --> 44:31.869
- I can dance and jump and move!
- Shh.

44:31.969 --> 44:33.704
You're calling
too much attention.

44:33.804 --> 44:36.306
Wait for me, Nana. Damn it.
Why are you in such a hurry?

44:36.407 --> 44:38.542
Geez.

44:39.743 --> 44:41.512
The mortician
just talked to us.

45:21.752 --> 45:23.554
Maria.

45:23.654 --> 45:25.155
Maria! Maria!

45:25.222 --> 45:27.091
No!

45:27.157 --> 45:28.992
Maria, don't do this
to me, please.

45:29.093 --> 45:30.594
Maria, no, damn it!

45:30.694 --> 45:32.529
Maria! No!

45:32.596 --> 45:33.997
Don't leave me.
Please.

45:34.064 --> 45:35.466
You have to come back.

45:35.566 --> 45:37.401
No!
Please breathe!

45:37.468 --> 45:39.636
Maria!
Maria, please don't leave me!

45:39.703 --> 45:41.371
Maria!

45:41.438 --> 45:42.806
Cut the whining.

45:42.873 --> 45:43.273
Please, please,
don't leave, Maria, no!

45:43.373 --> 45:45.409
Don't!

45:49.947 --> 45:53.717
You son of a bitch.
Son of a bitch.

45:55.753 --> 45:59.356
Don't you...
don't ever do this.

45:59.423 --> 46:03.193
Don't get inside my head.

46:03.293 --> 46:06.997
Don't you mess
with my freaking head!

46:08.365 --> 46:10.167
Four boys have died.

46:10.234 --> 46:12.770
It was a goddamn accident!

46:12.836 --> 46:15.906
Your plan was to burn down
the nightclub.

46:16.006 --> 46:19.009
They were there, but I...
I didn't see them.

46:20.444 --> 46:23.413
The life of a child is valuable.

46:28.685 --> 46:31.555
If you fail me again,

46:31.655 --> 46:34.758
that... will be real.

47:39.456 --> 47:43.994
♪♪♪

48:30.007 --> 48:33.043
[phone ringing]

48:35.946 --> 48:38.415
[wings fluttering]

48:38.482 --> 48:40.984
[ringing continues]

48:51.828 --> 48:54.665
[ringing continues]

49:01.872 --> 49:05.976
♪♪♪
